title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.1: SOCIAL PROTECTION AND SOCIAL/ECONOMIC SECTORS

description.narrative: Output 4.1: Social service demand is strengthened through modelling of evidence-based linkages between social protection and social/economic sectors (including health, nutrition, protection, energy and HIV) in select counties, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 - Social inclusion: An increased number of children from the poorest & most vulnerable households benefit from shock- responsive & integrated social protection interventions, as well as from child-specific policies

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, a disability-inclusive cash plus programme was introduced and covered a total of 3,019 children in Mombasa County. Furthermore, the progressive realization of universal social protection was advanced through work on the introduction of a Universal Child Benefit (UCB), including kick-starting a UCB pilot combining cash and services targeting 8300 children. UNICEF continued to engage with the government and partners to strengthen solid linkages between the social protection system and other key sectors such as health and health financing, nutrition, education, and child protection, while making the sector more inclusive, notably on disability and gender. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/12/2021
